      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: "In Deep in Crete" reminded me of a trip my wife and I took through the Samaria Gorge several years ago.</p>
        <p>After traversing the gorge on a 90-degree day in August and ending up in Agia Roumeli at 4 P.M., we boarded a ferry to the small seaside town of Agia Galini.  Not wishing to return to Camea by bus that evening, we found a Class E hotel, the only place available that night.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: "In Deep in Crete" reminded me of a trip my wife and I took through the Samaria Gorge several years ago.</p>
        <p>After traversing the gorge on a 90-degree day in August and ending up in Agia Roumeli at 4 P.M., we boarded a ferry to the small seaside town of Agia Galini.  Not wishing to return to Camea by bus that evening, we found a Class E hotel, the only place available that night.</p>
        <p>This hotel had the distinction of having a shower head directly over the commode. I will always have fond memories of this hotel and bathroom fixtures.</p>
        <p>ELLIOT J. MORITZ Chestnut Ridge, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
